That year the cold months stretched 74 days from first snow to last frost. Bit kept a careful tally: 296 acorns in the basket by the wall at the start, and they drew 2 acorns from it every morning, swaggering through the underbrush of their planning. Chirp, hidden in the dry stalks, had begun the winter with only 6 acorns in his jar, and chewed through 2 acorns a day. The count, of course, cannot go below zero for either of them.

