It is the way of the Ant to gather, and the way of the Grasshopper to play.

Snow had drifted high over the meadow grass, and inside the warm burrow Tic the ant sat beside a hole of seeds that he had hauled in all summer. He counted them out: 66 seeds in all. By his careful rule he would eat just 4 seeds each day, no more, no less. The wind howled outside and Tic sat content in her quiet life, working out how long the hole would carry him.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many whole days Tic's stockpile will last.
