Whisker the hare bounded down the path with a smug grin, sure that he would win without effort. By the time he had run 8 miles ahead, he could no longer see Slowpoke behind. He was drowsy from the warm sun, and curled up under an old oak to rest. Slowpoke the tortoise, far behind, kept on with eyes always on the path at a steady 4 miles per hour. He slept while Slowpoke walked for 2 hours without pause.

Question: who is in the lead by the time Whisker wakes up?
