It is the way of the Ant to gather, and the way of the Grasshopper to play.

In the long blue hour after noon, with snow piled to the rafters, Toc sat by a small lamp and went over the inventory once again. The basket that held the winter's food contained exactly 115 nuts. She measured out 2 nuts as a single day's portion — that was the rule she had set for herself when summer was bright. Now she only had to work out how many days the supply would carry her.

Question: how many whole days Toc's stockpile will last?
<|end|>
