Strength shared is strength multiplied — a truth the Lion knew well, and worked patiently to undo.

In a wide clearing rimmed by tall, bristling grass, what had once been 10 bulls grazing in a loose ring was now a scattered remnant. Roar the lion had taken 3 of them through the long campaign — each one alone, each one on a different day. The bulls that remained stood with growing alarm at separate corners of the clearing, refusing to look at one another. He crouched in the shadow of a stump untroubled by what others thought and totaled how many bulls were still standing.

