Rex the dog had been given 7 biscuits by the baker's wife, who tied them into a soft little cloth bundle that he carried gently in his mouth. On the plank bridge over the brook the bundle dipped down toward the water, and there in the ripples he saw a second dog with what looked like a fatter bundle. His mouth watering at the thought of more, he lunged — and one biscuit slipped out of the loose corner of the cloth and dropped, lost in the current.

