The Lion stalked the field where the Bulls had grazed in peace for many seasons. This was at the edge of the garden.

In the heart of an open meadow stood 5 bulls, each tested at the spring tournament to be of strength 3. Mane the lion watched from the long grass untroubled by what others thought, her own measured strength known to be 7. Bull by bull, she could outmatch any one of them one-on-one. But when the bulls had stood shoulder to shoulder, their unified strength came to 15 — too great for any single lion. The question now was simply whether the lion's only winning path lay through dividing the herd.

Question: whether Mane can defeat each bull alone (lion-strength > bull-strength) yet would lose against the herd combined (lion-strength < combined-strength)?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
{"tool_calls":[{"name":"eval","args":{"form":"(let [lion-strength 7 bulls 5 bull-strength 3 combined-strength (* bulls bull-strength)] (and (> lion-strength bull-strength) (< lion-strength combined-strength)))"}}]}
<|end|>


