Whisk stored 18 acorns under a loose floorboard of her burrow, happy with what she had that the oak above would drop more in autumn. Down in a cool city cellar, Nibble brooded over 7 butter pats stolen one by one from a dairy crock, his thoughts already on more and watchful of the cat. Neither could quite agree on whose larder was larger, only that the gap between them mattered.

Write a Clojure expression that computes the absolute difference between Whisk and Nibble's food counts.
<|end|>
