On a hilltop pasture, each of the 3 bulls had been weighed and trial-tested by the elder bulls in younger years, and each carried strength 8. Mane the lion, with strength 8, paced the ridge saying very little. Alone, a bull would not stand against her; but pressed together, the herd's combined strength rose to 24, beyond anything one cat could meet. The bulls already paced apart, with growing alarm, no longer sure of one another. Whether the lion needed them divided to win was the only remaining question.

