The market square smelled of dust and overripe fruit when Renard slunk between the stalls, dreaming of the next meal. A merchant's high display hung clusters of dark plums above the heads of the passing crowd. He chose a moment when no one was watching and rose up on hind paws — a stretch of 3 feet — and judged that a leap could lift him another 3 feet into the laden air. The plums swung lazily, and Renard thought hard about how high he could truly reach.

Write a Clojure expression that computes the highest point Renard can reach with a single leap.
