The kitchen-girl had counted out 4 biscuits into a cloth and sent Rex the dog off with them, saying not to lose a single one. On the bridge over the brook he caught sight of another dog in the water with what seemed an even fuller cloth, and with a hungry gleam in his eye, snapped at the rival. One biscuit slipped free and was swallowed by the brown water. When he came back to the kitchen, wishing she had been more careful, the count was short by exactly the difference between what had been promised and what actually arrived.

