There was once an extraordinary goose whose every morning gift was a single egg of pure gold.

In the lull after sundown, Morgan liked to pull out the farm ledger and look at how the week had gone for Honk the goose. The 4 days' counts read 1, 1, 1, 5. They stared at the column, grateful for every bite, working out a single steady-day figure — rounded down to a whole egg — for the bird's average yield.

Write a Clojure expression that computes the average eggs per day, rounded down to a whole number.
