It is said that the foolish Dog will trade what is real for what is only an image.

Rex the dog had been allowed exactly 9 bread chunks from the morning loaf by the baker's wife, who had arranged them carefully on a low plank for him to carry home. On the brook crossing the water mirrored him, and his eyes greedy with want, he lunged at the seeming rival's mouthful. One soft chunk fell into the brook and dissolved at once. He reached the doorstep, regretting every careless step, and the loaf-keeper saw plainly the gap between the careful count and the count that actually arrived.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many bread chunks Rex fell short by, compared to what he expected to bring home.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
I subtract the actual count (one fewer) from the expected count to find the gap.

{"tool_calls":[{"name":"eval","args":{"form":"(let [expected-bones 9 actual-bones (dec expected-bones)] (- expected-bones actual-bones))"}}]}
<|end|>


