The Hare loved nothing better than the sound of his own boasts; the Tortoise, nothing better than a long quiet walk. This was on the road.

A farmer leaning on his fence watched the racers go past. Pip flew by swaggering through the underbrush at 8 miles per hour; Mossback came behind at a calm 2 miles per hour, with steady, careful steps. Some while later the farmer wandered down the road and found Pip a clear 36 miles ahead of Mossback. He scratched his beard and tried to work out how long they had been running.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many whole hours they had been running.
<|end|>
