By the kitchen fire each evening, Bess emptied her day's earnings from a leather pouch and counted them out on the hearthstone. The cow had cost her 200 coins — a sum that had emptied her savings. Now the cow gave 3 cups a day; each cup brought home 4 coins. His thoughts already on more, she stacked the coins into little piles and watched the pouch grow no faster than the days went by.

Question: the smallest whole number of days until Bess fully recovers the cost of the cow?
